  "body": "**What this PR does / why we need it**:\nThis patch implements similar global flags + env to `kubectl --as=user --as-group=admins --as-group=operators` for helm.\nThe equivalent flags look like `helm --kube-as-user=user --kube-as-group=admins --kube-as-group=operators`.\n\nFixes #5303\n\n**Special notes for your reviewer**:\nThe flags were prefixed with `kube-` -- this follows the existing flags and was mentioned in this commment:\n> We will probably want to preface the flags with --kube- to match with the current convention (like how kubectl's --context flag matches with Helm's --kube-context flag).\n> https://github.com/helm/helm/issues/5304#issuecomment-551306428\n\nI also prepended an extra commit which updates the complete list of global ENV vars for the root CLI help-text.\n\n**If applicable**:\n- [*] this PR contains documentation\n- [*] this PR contains unit tests\n- [*] this PR has been tested for backwards compatibility\n\nChanges:\n- Support impersonation via flags similar to kubectl --as=\"user\"\n- Document all env vars for CLI help",
